Here is the Python code according to your specifications:

```python
def prime_factors(lst):
    num = lst[132]
    factors = set()
    i = 2
    while i * i <= num:
        if num % i:
            i += 1
        else:
            num //= i
            factors.add(i)
    if num > 1:
        factors.add(num)
    return factors
```
This function calculates the prime factors of the integer at index 132 in the input list by dividing the number by increasing integers until it cannot be divided anymore. The set of all numbers by which the original number was divided are the prime factors. The function returns this set.
